WEBVTT

00:01.377 --> 00:02.879
NARRATOR:
Previously on Prison Break:

00:03.045 --> 00:04.714
LINCOLN:
I didn't kill that man, Michael.

00:04.881 --> 00:06.841
MICHAEL:
If you didn't kill Terrence Steadman...

00:07.008 --> 00:09.010
...how did someone
make it look like you did?

00:09.177 --> 00:11.345
- I'm getting you out of here.
- That's impossible.

00:11.512 --> 00:13.514
Not if you designed the place, it isn't.

00:20.646 --> 00:21.689
[LAUGHING]

00:28.070 --> 00:30.156
[PANTING]

00:34.118 --> 00:35.369
It better be open, bro.

00:35.536 --> 00:37.038
SARA:
You're asking me to break the law.

00:37.205 --> 00:38.456
I ask you to make a mistake.

00:38.623 --> 00:40.458
Forget to lock up.

00:41.500 --> 00:42.793
We're in.

00:49.175 --> 00:50.801
Who killed Terrence Steadman?

00:51.469 --> 00:53.638
Nobody.
Terrence Steadman's still alive.

00:53.888 --> 00:55.181
Hello, Terrence.

00:55.514 --> 00:56.557
Sound the alarm.

00:56.724 --> 00:58.768
[ALARM WAILING]

01:06.275 --> 01:07.944
[TALKING INDISTINCTLY]

01:08.110 --> 01:09.737
[GRUNTING]

01:09.904 --> 01:11.948
[MAN 1 SCREAMS]

01:14.659 --> 01:17.161
ALL:
Hey! Hey!

01:19.705 --> 01:22.041
MAN 2:
No! No!

01:22.541 --> 01:25.419
- What do we do now?
- We run.

01:33.261 --> 01:34.679
MAHONE:
The escapees, who were they?

01:35.221 --> 01:37.181
MAN:
Got a list right here.

01:37.348 --> 01:38.599
Read it to me, if you could.

01:39.475 --> 01:42.144
MAN:
Michael Scofield, structural engineer.

01:42.311 --> 01:44.438
<i>Five years for armed robbery.</i>

01:44.605 --> 01:46.524
Benjamin Miles Franklin.

01:47.233 --> 01:51.237
<i>Former U.S. Army. Eight years
for possession of stolen goods.</i>

01:52.280 --> 01:53.823
John Abruzzi.

01:56.117 --> 01:58.536
<i>Don of the crime family
of the same name.</i>

01:58.703 --> 02:02.081
Life without parole for conspiracy
to commit murder.

02:02.665 --> 02:04.875
<i>Charles "Haywire" Patoshik.</i>

02:06.002 --> 02:08.878
Sixty years for second-degree murder.

02:09.422 --> 02:11.173
Fernando Sucre.

02:12.925 --> 02:15.970
<i>Five years for aggravated robbery.</i>

02:16.637 --> 02:18.306
David "Tweener" Apolskis.

02:19.640 --> 02:22.393
<i>Five years for grand larceny.</i>

02:23.561 --> 02:25.813
Theodore "T-Bag" Bagwell.

02:27.857 --> 02:31.444
Life for six counts of kidnapping,
rape and first-degree murder.

02:33.529 --> 02:34.822
And Lincoln Burrows.

02:39.702 --> 02:43.122
<i>Scheduled to die next week for the
murder of President Reynolds' brother.</i>

02:46.250 --> 02:48.836
MAHONE: How long has it been
since they got over the wall?

02:49.003 --> 02:51.172
<i>MAN:
Eight o'clock last night.</i>

02:51.339 --> 02:55.343
- Scofield. He and Burrows are brothers.
- That's right.

02:56.344 --> 02:58.596
<i>MAHONE". And he's the mastermind
of this whole thing.</i>

02:58.763 --> 03:00.556
MAN:
That's what they're saying.

03:01.390 --> 03:04.101
I want everything they've got on him.

03:13.652 --> 03:15.363
[DOGS BARKING]

03:22.411 --> 03:24.497
[OFFICERS SHOUTING INDISTINCTLY]

03:39.762 --> 03:41.430
LINCOLN:
Where are they?

03:42.890 --> 03:44.683
What the hell is that?

03:45.142 --> 03:47.228
[RUMBLING]

03:47.395 --> 03:49.480
[TRAIN WHISTLE BLOWING]

03:51.232 --> 03:52.900
Let's go.

03:57.196 --> 03:59.323
- We gotta make it to the other side!
SUCRE: What?

03:59.490 --> 04:00.991
- Make it to the other side!
SUCRE: You crazy?

04:04.453 --> 04:07.706
- Come on!
- Come on, run!

04:11.627 --> 04:15.714
LINCOLN: We gotta go! Run! Let's go!
Move it, move it!

04:16.589 --> 04:17.632
Go!

04:17.800 --> 04:19.635
FRANKLIN:
The thing is gaining speed, man!

04:22.763 --> 04:24.682
- It's going too fast!
- Go through!

04:24.849 --> 04:27.059
- What?
- Go through!

04:29.353 --> 04:30.896
SUCRE:
Michael!

04:32.398 --> 04:33.649
OFFICER 1:
Hold your fire!

04:43.200 --> 04:47.037
Freeze! I will gun you down, Scofield!

04:50.833 --> 04:51.876
Michael, come on.

04:52.042 --> 04:53.335
[GUNSHOT]

05:05.639 --> 05:07.057
Where's the aerial unit?

05:07.224 --> 05:09.393
OFFICER 2:
They're back on the ground refueling.

05:11.061 --> 05:12.271
Son of a bitch.

05:48.182 --> 05:51.644
FOLEY:
Sir, the media is ready.

06:09.078 --> 06:11.080
[SIGHS]

06:21.382 --> 06:26.428
I'd like to talk about John Wilkes Booth
for a moment, if I could.

06:26.595 --> 06:28.514
Abraham Lincoln's killer.

06:28.681 --> 06:30.307
Twelve days.

06:30.474 --> 06:32.685
That's how long it took to find him.

06:32.851 --> 06:36.397
In his journal during this period, he wrote
that the shadow was his friend...

06:36.564 --> 06:38.232
...the night his domain.

06:39.775 --> 06:42.111
<i>He acknowledged
that neuroses driving the criminal...</i>

06:42.278 --> 06:44.947
<i>...to commit the original crime
is compounded...</i>

06:45.990 --> 06:48.659
<i>...magnified by flight.</i>

06:49.201 --> 06:52.204
<i>By the sounds of dogs at his heels.</i>

06:52.663 --> 06:54.206
Fear becomes paranoia.

06:55.165 --> 06:57.209
<i>Paranoia, ultimately psychosis.</i>

06:59.086 --> 07:02.548
I bring this up because in 140 years...

07:02.715 --> 07:06.594
...the fundamental mind
of the escaped man has not changed.

07:06.760 --> 07:11.432
The escaped man is still human,
he is still afraid...

07:11.599 --> 07:14.893
...and he will stop at nothing
in his attempted flight.

07:16.312 --> 07:17.855
<i>Fortunately for us...</i>

07:18.022 --> 07:23.944
<i>...while our quarry has shadow
and night as his ally...</i>

07:24.111 --> 07:26.739
...we have something far greater.

07:27.948 --> 07:29.783
Television.

07:30.200 --> 07:32.953
I would encourage everyone
who is watching...

07:33.370 --> 07:36.790
...everyone in this country,
to take a good look at these faces.

07:37.333 --> 07:41.670
These men right here are now
the eight most wanted men in America.

07:48.802 --> 07:52.473
I thought I thought this out.
You saw all those guys back there?

07:52.640 --> 07:54.892
The key is they're back there
and we're up here.

07:55.059 --> 07:56.769
SUCRE: Yeah. And how long
is that gonna last?

07:56.935 --> 07:59.146
Especially since we don't have
a pot to piss in...

07:59.313 --> 08:01.482
...thanks to Abruzzi's
magically disappearing jet.

08:01.649 --> 08:03.651
You were never gonna be
on that plane.

08:03.817 --> 08:05.819
Don't think I don't know
where you were going.

08:05.986 --> 08:08.155
- Where am I going?
FRANKLIN: Oh, I don't know.

08:08.322 --> 08:09.823
Utah?

08:10.866 --> 08:12.910
You planning on
telling us about the money?

08:13.285 --> 08:14.620
What money?

08:15.204 --> 08:18.916
Five million dollars that Westmoreland
planted in the desert in Utah.

08:20.626 --> 08:24.421
- You don't know what you're saying.
- You wish I didn't know.

08:24.588 --> 08:26.131
Wait, wait. What money?

08:29.176 --> 08:30.386
MAHONE:
Warden.

08:31.595 --> 08:34.765
POPE: It's a little early for the FBI
to be showing up, don't you think?

08:35.015 --> 08:37.142
Look, I get it. It's still your investigation.

08:37.308 --> 08:40.479
Once those criminals cross state lines,
it'll become a federal matter.

08:40.645 --> 08:43.607
- Yeah, well, that is not gonna happen.
- I hope you're right.

08:43.774 --> 08:47.486
That's why I suggest we cut through
any interagency politics from the outset.

08:47.653 --> 08:50.489
- Full transparency.
- Absolutely.

08:50.656 --> 08:52.074
Good.

08:52.241 --> 08:55.035
Then maybe you can tell me
about Dr. Tancredi.

08:55.619 --> 08:57.621
There's nothing to tell.

08:57.788 --> 09:00.999
From what I'm hearing,
she may have abetted the escapees.

09:01.166 --> 09:03.669
Opened the door
that allowed them to get out.

09:03.961 --> 09:07.631
- Like I said, there's nothing to tell.
- Not being very transparent, warden.

09:07.798 --> 09:11.552
- Look, I don't discuss my staff.
- Maybe you should...

09:11.719 --> 09:14.012
...because she may be the key
to this thing.

09:15.055 --> 09:17.558
We need to speak with her.

09:18.559 --> 09:23.147
Well, right now, Mr. Mahone,
she's not gonna speak with anyone.

09:30.654 --> 09:31.905
DOCTOR 1:
How we doing?

09:32.072 --> 09:34.324
DOCTOR 2:
Well, the IVs are hydrating her.

09:34.491 --> 09:38.203
We've got her on naloxone infusion.
Half-milligram per hour.

09:38.370 --> 09:40.706
DOCTOR 1:
What do you think the chances are?

09:40.873 --> 09:43.876
DOCTOR 2: Well, we've done everything
on our end. It's really up to her.

09:44.042 --> 09:48.922
Either she fights and lives,
or she quits and dies.

10:19.453 --> 10:20.537
[GAS PS]

10:39.807 --> 10:41.767
Hey, what do you think--?

10:46.438 --> 10:48.440
Do whatever thing
you've gotta do, man.

10:53.487 --> 10:57.157
Oh, and boy...

10:58.408 --> 11:01.161
If you call the cops,
I will put this thing right here...

11:02.746 --> 11:04.665
...in your eye.

11:09.002 --> 11:10.838
Thank you.

11:23.725 --> 11:25.018
[DOGS BARKING]

11:28.105 --> 11:30.190
MAHONE:
Structural engineer, huh?

11:30.357 --> 11:32.943
Not the kind you'd expect
to get that much ink.

11:33.110 --> 11:34.361
Not the kind at all.

11:35.362 --> 11:38.574
How long do you think it'd take
to get something like that done?

11:38.740 --> 11:41.201
A hundred hours. Two hundred.

11:41.368 --> 11:44.997
Tattoo artist who gave it to him must've
spent a lot of time with him, then.

11:46.039 --> 11:47.749
I'll find out who it was.

11:51.461 --> 11:53.171
- Mr. Bellick.
- Don't talk to me.

11:53.338 --> 11:55.716
Fine. But it's gonna make
collaboration kind of hard.

11:55.883 --> 11:58.719
Collaboration?
I got men out here in harm's way...

11:58.886 --> 12:00.721
...and you're giving press conferences.

12:00.888 --> 12:02.347
The press is a tool.

12:02.514 --> 12:05.017
It'll bring those men back quicker
than bloodhounds will.

12:05.183 --> 12:06.518
We don't need you.

12:06.685 --> 12:09.646
We're hot on their trail, it's a matter
of time till we nail them.

12:09.813 --> 12:12.065
The problem I find
with being on a trail...

12:12.232 --> 12:15.402
...is that, by definition,
you'll always be behind your prey.

12:17.696 --> 12:19.656
We'll see about that.

12:27.039 --> 12:28.373
TERRENCE:
I'm not armed.

12:28.540 --> 12:31.752
VERONICA: You'll have to excuse me if
I'm a little short on trust at the moment.

12:31.919 --> 12:35.672
I assure you, young woman,
I'm the furthest thing from a threat.

12:35.839 --> 12:38.425
I think the Percocet
pretty much ensures that.

12:38.592 --> 12:43.180
Good. Then you won't mind
if I capture this moment for posterity.

12:43.347 --> 12:45.432
Won't do you any good.

12:45.766 --> 12:48.894
You don't care that somebody's
gonna be executed for your murder?

12:49.061 --> 12:51.855
I'm not the one who chose
Lincoln Burrows as the fall guy.

12:52.022 --> 12:53.482
Who did?

12:53.649 --> 12:55.025
Your sister, the president?

12:55.192 --> 12:57.778
You don't understand.
I'm a prisoner to all of this.

12:57.945 --> 13:00.113
Oh, come on.
You could've come forward.

13:00.280 --> 13:02.991
You could've stopped this thing
before it even got started.

13:03.158 --> 13:05.452
No, I really am a prisoner.

13:05.619 --> 13:07.162
And now you are too.

13:08.747 --> 13:11.291
The moment you let the door
shut behind you.

13:19.508 --> 13:22.052
Didn't it strike you as curious...

13:22.219 --> 13:24.137
...that there wasn't any security
out there?

13:24.304 --> 13:26.890
The doors only open from the outside.

13:27.057 --> 13:30.435
The glass is <i>2</i> inches thick, bulletproof.

13:32.729 --> 13:35.148
There's no getting out of here,
young woman.

13:39.861 --> 13:41.446
LINCOLN:
We gotta dump them now.

13:41.989 --> 13:45.075
Can't. They know about Utah.

13:45.242 --> 13:46.785
All the more reason to dump them.

13:46.952 --> 13:50.831
If they get caught, the feds will know
where we're going. They'll tell them.

13:50.998 --> 13:54.334
We just gotta make sure they stay afloat
till we're off in Utah.

13:54.501 --> 13:56.461
Doing what we gotta do.

13:57.963 --> 14:00.549
You really think
the money's gonna be there?

14:02.009 --> 14:04.761
Charles might have had
a flexible relationship with the truth...

14:04.928 --> 14:09.182
...but at the end... At the end,
there'd be no reason for him to lie.

14:10.017 --> 14:12.853
I figure once we bag it,
we cross over into Mexico.

14:13.186 --> 14:17.149
Take a whole bunch of bumpy
second-class bus rides till we hit Panama.

14:17.524 --> 14:19.818
LINCOLN:
You really got a fix on this dive shop?

14:19.985 --> 14:21.194
MICHAEL:
Yeah.

14:22.404 --> 14:25.991
Right now, I wouldn't mind swinging
in a hammock for the next 10, 20 years.

14:26.700 --> 14:30.120
We got half the country after us.
We ain't making it to Panama or Utah.

14:30.287 --> 14:31.496
Not without help.

14:33.540 --> 14:35.208
Veronica can't help us.

14:35.375 --> 14:36.626
How can you say that?

14:36.793 --> 14:39.713
- We don't have money, clothes--
- We got all that.

14:40.714 --> 14:42.382
I thought the plan was Abruzzi's jet.

14:42.549 --> 14:44.009
Abruzzi's jet was plan A.

14:45.719 --> 14:47.804
- Then we got--
- Everything we need.

14:47.971 --> 14:49.389
Where?

14:50.182 --> 14:52.100
Storage.

15:01.568 --> 15:03.570
<i>MAHONE:
Scofield designed the tattoo, not you?</i>

15:03.737 --> 15:06.573
He brought the entire thing in.
Every element.

15:06.740 --> 15:09.326
I mean, look at it.
It's the frigging Sistine Chapel.

15:09.493 --> 15:11.453
I know the guy was an engineer,
but, man...

15:11.620 --> 15:14.289
...his skill as an artist
was unbelievable.

15:14.456 --> 15:16.917
What else? What can you tell me
about him as a person?

15:17.084 --> 15:19.211
Uh, he was cool, you know.

15:19.377 --> 15:22.714
But talk about a detail Nazi.
Everything had to be perfect.

15:22.881 --> 15:26.593
Exactly as he drew it.
I always sort of had the feeling...

15:26.760 --> 15:31.223
...that the whole thing was some sort
of inside joke that only he was in on.

15:35.435 --> 15:36.812
We have your number, right?

15:37.062 --> 15:38.563
Yeah.

15:39.147 --> 15:41.858
I may be calling you. Thank you.

15:44.444 --> 15:46.071
Foley.

15:48.490 --> 15:50.784
What was the name of that road
to get to the prison?

15:50.951 --> 15:52.452
FOLEY:
I think it was English Street.

15:56.790 --> 15:59.584
In front of the prison,
the two streets that intersect with it?

15:59.751 --> 16:02.963
- Fitz and Percy. Why?
- Thank you.

16:06.466 --> 16:08.969
- Saddle up.
FRANKLIN: Where we going?

16:09.136 --> 16:12.180
Somewhere we can stop being cons
and start being civilians.

16:12.347 --> 16:16.560
Yo, why don't you cut out all the riddles,
Snowflake, and give it to us straight?

16:16.726 --> 16:18.145
What?

16:21.148 --> 16:24.067
GRACE: Hi.
- Hi.

16:25.110 --> 16:28.113
Well, hey, little one.

16:28.280 --> 16:29.906
What are you doing?

16:30.073 --> 16:31.867
Well, uh...

16:32.993 --> 16:34.744
We're just fishing.

16:35.996 --> 16:37.414
With no poles?

16:37.956 --> 16:40.375
Well, we like to fish with our hands.

16:40.542 --> 16:43.170
Yeah, that's it. Hand-fishing.

16:43.336 --> 16:45.964
I think the question is...

16:47.465 --> 16:50.427
...what are you doing out here?

16:51.303 --> 16:53.096
- Hunting.
HUNTER: Gracie?

16:53.638 --> 16:56.349
Get away, Gracie. Get away. Get back.

16:56.516 --> 16:57.851
Whoa. Whoa, whoa.

16:58.018 --> 16:59.519
You're those guys from Fox River.

17:00.687 --> 17:02.814
Don't any of you move
a freaking muscle.

17:11.865 --> 17:14.159
Get away from her.
Get away from her!

17:14.326 --> 17:16.828
Okay, okay. Just relax.

17:17.119 --> 17:18.914
Relax.

17:19.497 --> 17:21.875
ABRUZZI: Sir...
- You stay where you are.

17:22.209 --> 17:24.877
LINCOLN: No, no! John!
- Put the gun down! Put the gun down.

17:25.045 --> 17:26.296
- Let her go!
- Right now!

17:26.463 --> 17:28.548
- Let her go!
- John, let go of the girl.

17:28.715 --> 17:30.300
- Shut up!
HUNTER: Let her go.

17:30.467 --> 17:33.136
ABRUZZI:
Put it down. Drop the gun.

17:33.887 --> 17:36.598
You drop the gun. Drop it now.

17:37.557 --> 17:39.017
You put the gun down.

17:40.393 --> 17:41.895
One...

17:42.604 --> 17:44.356
I'm gonna pull the trigger.

17:44.522 --> 17:46.066
TWO!

17:48.902 --> 17:52.239
Good boy. Good boy.

17:52.822 --> 17:54.407
Get the gun.

17:54.574 --> 17:56.326
Pick it up!

17:58.578 --> 18:00.705
- Don't you hurt her. Don't you lay a--
ABRUZZI: Hey!

18:01.039 --> 18:03.083
Gonna be all right.

18:03.250 --> 18:04.960
Right?

18:07.087 --> 18:08.672
Run to Daddy.

18:11.132 --> 18:13.051
I ain't gonna say anything
to anybody, man.

18:13.218 --> 18:16.012
MICHAEL: You're not gonna get hurt,
so just calm down. Where's your car?

18:16.179 --> 18:18.348
- Up on the road.
MICHAEL: I need your keys.

18:31.403 --> 18:33.405
You're being considered
an accessory to this.

18:33.571 --> 18:35.782
You know that, don't you?

18:36.283 --> 18:38.285
I know very little right now.

18:38.451 --> 18:41.788
You opened the door to the infirmary
that allowed Scofield to escape.

18:41.955 --> 18:44.291
- Didn't you?
- No.

18:44.457 --> 18:47.043
- You have a sexual relationship with him?
- No.

18:47.210 --> 18:49.796
But you had feelings for him.

18:50.380 --> 18:52.132
Seven other men got out, you know.

18:54.759 --> 18:56.136
Who?

19:08.732 --> 19:10.817
[DOOR BELL RINGS
AND DOOR CLOSES]

19:11.401 --> 19:14.154
I'm sorry, sir, it's Saturday.
We're not open.

19:14.321 --> 19:16.531
Well, that's sort of the point.

19:16.698 --> 19:17.991
Sorry, sir?

19:18.158 --> 19:23.580
See, I'm gonna need some work done
and I'm gonna need it done, uh, privately.

19:23.747 --> 19:25.874
I'm sorry,
you said you needed the work done?

19:27.917 --> 19:30.003
This is a medical clinic, isn't it?

19:30.170 --> 19:32.255
Well, of course it is, sir,
but for animals.

19:32.422 --> 19:33.673
[CAT MEOWS]

19:37.177 --> 19:38.678
God, man, what happened to you?

19:38.845 --> 19:40.847
You need medical attention.

19:41.014 --> 19:42.474
- No.
- I'm gonna get an ambulance.

19:44.059 --> 19:45.518
[GAS PS]

19:46.019 --> 19:48.980
Nobody's gonna be doing
any calling here, doctor.

19:49.147 --> 19:50.690
Fine.

19:51.733 --> 19:53.318
That's right.

19:53.568 --> 19:55.528
What do you want?

20:02.369 --> 20:03.995
FRANKLIN:
You know what? That's it.

20:04.162 --> 20:08.041
I want Eyetie out of the car right now,
man. That was a little girl.

20:08.208 --> 20:10.085
Don't you have a heart?

20:10.794 --> 20:12.962
God, I have a daughter.
I have a little girl.

20:13.630 --> 20:15.673
I got one too.

20:16.424 --> 20:19.219
But if I hadn't done
what I had to do...

20:19.386 --> 20:21.763
...we wouldn't be on our way
to see them right now.

20:22.389 --> 20:24.224
Turn right up there.

20:24.391 --> 20:26.518
FRANKLIN:
Whoa, hold on. Where we going?

20:26.684 --> 20:28.395
MICHAEL:
Oswego.

20:28.561 --> 20:32.023
That's west, man. We need to go east.
My family's back in Chicago.

20:32.190 --> 20:34.192
And you think
the cops don't know about it?

20:35.026 --> 20:36.945
You think they're not just sitting there...

20:37.112 --> 20:40.240
...waiting for you
to come running back home?

20:40.824 --> 20:42.367
What's the matter with you?

20:42.534 --> 20:44.828
SUCRE: What about New York?
- What about it?

20:44.994 --> 20:46.246
My girl's pregnant, bro.

20:46.413 --> 20:50.834
Understand,
your love is your weakness right now.

20:51.000 --> 20:52.043
And they know about it.

20:52.210 --> 20:53.795
MICHAEL:
Doesn't mean it has to stop you.

20:54.295 --> 20:56.423
You just gotta be smart about it.

20:57.090 --> 20:58.842
And get to Oswego.

20:59.008 --> 21:01.594
Oswego is not on the way, Snowflake.

21:01.761 --> 21:04.431
MICHAEL:
It's not where Oswego is.

21:05.890 --> 21:07.976
It's what's in Oswego.

21:08.393 --> 21:12.397
Captain, Scofields credit-card
transaction history.

21:12.564 --> 21:15.024
Spent money in Will County
before he was incarcerated.

21:15.191 --> 21:17.152
- Exactly.
- He's from Chicago.

21:17.318 --> 21:19.070
Why does a guy
from Chicago come here...

21:19.237 --> 21:21.614
...and spend 8 grand
in all these places in a month?

21:21.781 --> 21:23.658
Car wash, voice mail,
storage, car rental.

21:23.825 --> 21:25.410
- We got guys looking into it.
- Good.

21:25.577 --> 21:28.121
- What about the feds? Should we tell?
- What do you think?

21:28.288 --> 21:29.747
Captain Bellick, we got something.

21:29.914 --> 21:33.251
Hunter up by Tamarack
just ran into five of the cons.

21:39.299 --> 21:40.967
MAHONE:
So this is where Scofield lived.

21:41.759 --> 21:45.555
IVES: Yeah, up until about two months
ago when he was incarcerated.

21:48.975 --> 21:51.895
Mother's dead, father's a deadbeat.

21:53.229 --> 21:56.483
Got nothing in the whole world
but your brother.

22:04.282 --> 22:06.493
So you plan.

22:15.752 --> 22:17.670
And you scheme for months...

22:20.256 --> 22:22.675
...until you get it right.

22:24.010 --> 22:27.180
Every single element.

22:34.354 --> 22:36.648
And then you destroy all the evidence.

22:48.576 --> 22:51.162
I want divers down in the river.

22:54.165 --> 22:56.376
TERRENCE:
You won't get cell coverage.

22:56.543 --> 22:58.711
We're in the middle of nowhere.

22:59.212 --> 23:03.383
Those digital carriers don't have towers
way out here in Western Montana.

23:03.550 --> 23:06.719
- How about shutting up, Terrence?
- Just trying to save you some effort.

23:06.886 --> 23:10.056
They're like a web, these people.
Harder you struggle, worse it gets.

23:10.223 --> 23:12.892
Sounds to me like a coward
trying to justify himself.

23:13.518 --> 23:16.396
If I stay out of the way and stay quiet,
I stay alive.

23:16.563 --> 23:18.731
That's what they said.
That's what they told me.

23:18.898 --> 23:21.693
And you want to live like this?
In a hermetically sealed box...

23:21.859 --> 23:25.738
...while everything outside goes to hell?
Self-preservation is a strong motivator.

23:26.573 --> 23:28.241
So's the truth.

23:32.287 --> 23:33.580
Don't.

23:35.331 --> 23:36.791
Young woman.

23:40.253 --> 23:41.921
Do not.

23:44.090 --> 23:45.800
Don't.

23:49.137 --> 23:50.430
How you doing, buddy?

23:50.597 --> 23:52.765
I'm pretty freaked out,
that's how I'm doing.

23:53.099 --> 23:54.559
They took your car, didn't they?

23:54.726 --> 23:56.060
1978 Grand Cherokee?

23:56.227 --> 23:57.979
- Yeah.
- Which way did they go?

23:58.146 --> 24:00.481
Up that way. North, toward Oswego.

24:00.648 --> 24:02.442
Oswego. Pardon me.

24:02.609 --> 24:04.402
Scofield's paperwork, get it to me.

24:04.569 --> 24:06.112
That credit card stuff.

24:06.279 --> 24:08.156
Right here, captain.

24:12.869 --> 24:14.454
Of course.

24:14.871 --> 24:18.124
Where else you gonna put
all the crap you need to disappear?

24:19.000 --> 24:21.628
We're going to Oswego, boys.

24:31.679 --> 24:33.097
You have a visitor.

24:34.307 --> 24:35.600
Thank you.

24:44.150 --> 24:45.860
Thanks.

24:47.820 --> 24:49.781
You look disappointed.

24:49.947 --> 24:52.283
No, I thought
you were gonna be my father.

24:53.034 --> 24:54.285
You heard from him?

24:55.411 --> 24:56.996
His office.

24:58.247 --> 25:01.751
Well, brought you a change of clothes.

25:02.960 --> 25:05.922
- Figured, you know.
- Thanks.

25:06.464 --> 25:07.757
And your purse.

25:08.132 --> 25:10.635
You left it in the infirmary.

25:17.934 --> 25:20.687
I'm in a lot of trouble, I think.

25:21.354 --> 25:23.272
I, um...

25:25.149 --> 25:28.653
I need to apologize to you.

25:41.499 --> 25:44.460
They threatened my job
if I didn't talk, and--

25:44.627 --> 25:46.838
No, no. No.

25:47.380 --> 25:49.716
One thing you learn
when you're walking the steps...

25:49.882 --> 25:53.302
...is that you never outsource the blame
that belongs in your own back yard.

25:56.264 --> 25:57.890
Well...

25:58.683 --> 26:02.145
...you're not the first correctional worker
that fell for a con.

26:02.311 --> 26:03.980
Trust me.

26:06.399 --> 26:08.317
He never cared.

26:09.777 --> 26:11.612
Not one bit.

26:18.202 --> 26:20.079
What are you thinking about?

26:20.371 --> 26:21.372
[SIGHS]

26:21.539 --> 26:23.040
Mistakes.

26:23.875 --> 26:25.710
You had to do it.

26:26.169 --> 26:28.129
MICHAEL:
Not like I did.

26:30.548 --> 26:32.091
I ruined her life.

26:33.134 --> 26:36.804
- Nothing you can do about it now.
- That's not true.

26:38.723 --> 26:41.058
You fell for her, huh?

26:43.019 --> 26:44.312
[MICHAEL CLEARS THROAT]

26:44.479 --> 26:46.272
Where's Oswego?

26:46.439 --> 26:48.524
Half a mile, maybe.

26:48.941 --> 26:50.568
Good.

26:52.278 --> 26:54.280
What are you gonna do, Terrence,
shoot me?

26:54.447 --> 26:56.949
Blow my guts all over the house?
Then what?

26:57.116 --> 26:59.118
You can't leave, remember?

26:59.285 --> 27:01.829
You kill me, you're stuck with me.

27:03.122 --> 27:04.457
I'm safe here.

27:04.624 --> 27:06.417
You're a prisoner here.

27:06.584 --> 27:08.795
TERRENCE:
But I'm still breathing.

27:10.171 --> 27:12.381
If I go outside...

27:12.548 --> 27:16.093
...one step, I won't be.

27:17.804 --> 27:20.890
You look at me like I'm the devil.

27:22.433 --> 27:25.061
I gave up my family.

27:26.145 --> 27:29.315
My teeth. I eat Percocet all day...

27:30.566 --> 27:32.819
...just to dull the pain
of my miserable existence.

27:32.985 --> 27:36.948
- You have no idea what I've been through.
- What you've been through?

27:38.574 --> 27:40.535
This isn't about you, Terrence.

27:41.452 --> 27:42.662
Don't.

27:46.999 --> 27:49.293
<i>MAN [ON PHONE]:
Blackfoot Sheriff's Depa/Tmenz'.</i>

27:50.169 --> 27:52.839
<i>Hello? Blackfoot Sheriff's Department.</i>

27:53.005 --> 27:54.507
Hello, my name's Veronica Donovan.

27:54.674 --> 27:58.469
I need you to send a unit to the house at
the end of Light Road as soon as possible.

27:58.636 --> 28:00.930
<i>I'm sorry, ma 'am,
are you calling to report a crime ?</i>

28:01.848 --> 28:03.140
Yeah.

28:03.307 --> 28:05.560
By the president of the United States.

28:07.520 --> 28:08.855
Send the car.

28:09.355 --> 28:11.566
I'm sorry, sir,
I don't think I can do this.

28:12.233 --> 28:14.318
There are nerves. Look...

28:14.485 --> 28:16.195
- You need a specialist.
- I don't--

28:16.362 --> 28:18.406
You need somebody
who knows what they're doing.

28:18.573 --> 28:20.533
I don't have the luxury of choice here.

28:20.700 --> 28:23.327
My hand has been in that box
for hours now. It is dying.

28:23.494 --> 28:25.079
Sir, I am not capable of doing this.

28:25.246 --> 28:29.208
I only have one hand, but I can stick this
in your neck before you get to that door.

28:29.375 --> 28:33.588
If that's not incentive enough for you,
I see you have a Mrs. Gudat out there.

28:33.754 --> 28:35.756
With a name like that
in a county like this...

28:35.923 --> 28:38.759
...old Mrs. Gudat would not be
too hard to find, now, would she?

28:39.510 --> 28:41.095
Fine.

28:41.721 --> 28:42.889
I can promise you nothing.

28:44.223 --> 28:46.517
Story of my life.

28:47.351 --> 28:48.686
I'll have to put you under.

28:50.771 --> 28:52.064
Do I really look that stupid?

28:52.231 --> 28:55.902
Sir, I cannot do a procedure like this
without an anesthetic.

28:56.068 --> 28:57.612
I have to cut away dead flesh.

28:57.778 --> 29:01.449
Nobody can undergo a procedure like this
without an anesthetic.

29:01.616 --> 29:05.244
I ain't nobody.

29:07.330 --> 29:11.667
Schweitzer was the company that made
the toilet Scofield took off to get out.

29:11.834 --> 29:15.338
- The Allen bolt was the fitting.
- It's all here, isn't it?

29:15.504 --> 29:18.174
AGENT: Yeah.
- It's amazing.

29:19.383 --> 29:22.345
Ripe Chance Woods. ls there a place
in the vicinity with that name?

29:22.511 --> 29:23.763
IVES:
Got someone looking into it.

29:23.930 --> 29:27.391
AGENT: DOCS moving on
a storage facility in Oswego.

29:33.439 --> 29:35.524
[OFFICERS SPEAKING INDISTINCTLY]

29:42.198 --> 29:47.286
Captain, manager says that Scofield's
got a lease on Unit 164. Still active.

29:47.453 --> 29:49.956
We have guys on 8th Street,
3rd Street and in the alley.

29:50.122 --> 29:53.334
- If they're in there, we got them boxed.
- We push right up the gut, then.

29:53.501 --> 29:56.212
Any one of them makes
a threatening move, put a hole in them.

29:56.379 --> 29:57.630
You got it.

29:59.090 --> 30:00.800
Officer.

30:03.761 --> 30:07.098
This is my collar, smart guy.
Back the hell off.

30:15.773 --> 30:17.733
MICHAEL:
Close the door.

30:23.155 --> 30:24.907
Still nothing on this place?

30:25.074 --> 30:26.784
Nope.
They're coming back with nothing.

30:28.911 --> 30:31.372
No place by that name anywhere
in this country...

30:32.123 --> 30:34.166
...or any other country for that matter.

30:47.888 --> 30:49.515
MICHAEL:
Let's go.

31:05.156 --> 31:07.825
PATTERSON:
Son of a bitch set us up.

31:40.858 --> 31:42.068
Not one word.

31:44.361 --> 31:45.780
Officer.

31:51.786 --> 31:53.370
Nothing.

31:54.914 --> 31:56.916
[CHUCKLES]

31:57.083 --> 31:59.210
Oh, that kid's clever.

31:59.376 --> 32:02.755
It's not a place, it's a name.

32:03.130 --> 32:06.300
- Your PDA, you got it?
- Yeah.

32:07.218 --> 32:09.762
Bring up the census of this county.

32:09.929 --> 32:11.972
Far back as it goes.

32:14.558 --> 32:18.062
- Well, somebody's gonna see us.
- Keep digging.

32:18.521 --> 32:21.732
We're gonna go to hell, guys.
Swear to God, we're gonna go to hell.

32:26.612 --> 32:28.280
MICHAEL:
Help me out.

32:35.913 --> 32:38.582
FRANKLIN:
You are one sick cat, you know that?

32:39.208 --> 32:40.835
[GRUNTING]

32:41.627 --> 32:43.420
IVES:
What are you looking for?

32:46.757 --> 32:48.884
We gotta go to the cemetery.

32:49.051 --> 32:50.261
Now.

32:57.059 --> 33:00.521
Originally, this was supposed to be a
week's worth of clothes for me and Linc.

33:00.688 --> 33:03.440
But I figured you all need
just as much help as we do, so...

33:03.607 --> 33:05.901
You're doing this
out of the goodness of your heart?

33:06.068 --> 33:08.779
Right, John, the heart.
You remember what that is, don't you?

33:08.946 --> 33:10.948
FRANKLIN:
Damn, Snowflake, this is tight, man.

33:11.115 --> 33:13.701
It's like I said,
we gotta stop being cons...

33:13.868 --> 33:15.578
...start being civilians.

33:33.596 --> 33:36.515
ABRUZZI: Nice. The trousers are
a little bit too short, don't you think?

33:37.183 --> 33:39.226
Chop your feet off. You're good at that.

33:39.393 --> 33:41.187
This jacket isn't exactly the best thing.

33:41.353 --> 33:44.356
- You know what I'm saying?
- You want variety, hit Target.

33:48.527 --> 33:49.820
Linc.

33:51.447 --> 33:52.656
What have we got?

33:53.157 --> 33:54.783
MICHAEL:
Money, passports...

33:56.118 --> 33:57.828
...prepaid phone cards.

33:58.495 --> 34:01.498
- Huh. Archie Ryan?
- You see mine?

34:01.665 --> 34:02.875
Phineas McClintock.

34:06.253 --> 34:08.005
Whoa, and these?

34:08.172 --> 34:11.926
Keys to a car that's waiting for us
a couple of hundred yards from here.

34:12.259 --> 34:13.677
That a two-of-us or five-of-us?

34:13.844 --> 34:15.596
That's a two-of-us.

34:16.222 --> 34:18.724
- They know?
- Not yet.

34:23.270 --> 34:25.272
Guys, guys. We got company.

35:16.240 --> 35:17.950
SUCRE:
We gotta roll.

35:18.534 --> 35:20.327
How did he know?

36:09.335 --> 36:11.670
We're civilians. Remember that.

36:11.837 --> 36:13.881
We're civilians.

36:16.008 --> 36:19.553
- I'm sorry. Do you know what time it is?
MICHAEL: No, I'm sorry.

36:34.902 --> 36:38.155
I can't go outside. They'll kill me
as soon as I show my face.

36:38.322 --> 36:39.490
You're wrong about that.

36:39.656 --> 36:42.618
As soon as you show your face,
this whole thing is gonna be over.

36:42.785 --> 36:44.495
You can have your life back, Terrence.

36:45.412 --> 36:47.706
- Promise?
- I promise.

36:48.624 --> 36:50.376
[PHONE RINGS]

36:50.542 --> 36:52.002
Hello?

36:52.169 --> 36:53.796
LINCOLN:
V, it's me.

36:53.962 --> 36:55.631
<i>- Linc?
- We're out.</i>

36:55.798 --> 36:59.051
Oh, thank God you're okay.
I saw the news. You gotta stop.

36:59.218 --> 37:01.303
<i>- I need you to turn yourself in.
- What?</i>

37:01.470 --> 37:05.307
I found Steadman.
I'm with him now, Linc. He's alive.

37:05.474 --> 37:06.850
You're gonna be exonerated.

37:07.726 --> 37:09.728
- Come in.
- Steadman?

37:09.895 --> 37:11.772
What are you talking,
you found Steadman?

37:12.439 --> 37:14.233
- Terrence, come on, let's go.
- Afternoon.

37:14.400 --> 37:16.110
- Ver0n/'ca.
- The police are here.

37:16.276 --> 37:18.445
Look, I need you
to stay where you are.

37:18.612 --> 37:20.697
- Ma'a'm.
- I don't wanna lose you.

37:20.864 --> 37:23.742
- Ma'am, put the phone down.
- What?

37:23.909 --> 37:26.662
Mr. Steadman, take a few steps back.

37:28.831 --> 37:30.040
Ver-- Veronica?

37:30.874 --> 37:32.251
<i>Veronica ?</i>

37:32.418 --> 37:34.002
Oh, my God.

37:34.795 --> 37:36.046
<i>Veronica!</i>

37:36.547 --> 37:38.632
[BREATHING HEAVILY]

38:16.879 --> 38:20.299
I thought you knew that all calls to
the local station are routed through us.

38:20.466 --> 38:22.676
- This is federal land, remember?
- Mm.

38:22.843 --> 38:27.389
And, uh, as for your little toy here.
It's contraband.

38:27.556 --> 38:31.685
- You gonna tell us how you got it there?
- I brought it when I got here.

38:32.978 --> 38:36.565
- Whatever for?
- To protect myself.

38:36.982 --> 38:40.027
That's what we're here for, remember?

39:49.930 --> 39:52.474
WOMAN <i>[ON</i> TV]: <i>/n less than a day,
the Ira/I has gone 00/0'...</i>

39:52.641 --> 39:55.102
<i>...in pursuit of what are
being called the Fox River Eight--</i>

39:55.269 --> 39:57.187
IVES:
That's fine. Stay on top of it, all right?

39:57.354 --> 40:00.399
DOC's still doing a sweep of Oswego
but they have basically vanished.

40:00.566 --> 40:04.069
- I wouldn't be sure about that, Mr. Ives.
- Don't know how you can be confident.

40:04.236 --> 40:06.446
It's not like they left a map
where they're going.

40:06.613 --> 40:09.241
Actually, that's exactly
what they did.

40:10.367 --> 40:12.995
Scofield had the entire thing on his body.

40:13.161 --> 40:16.415
<i>How to get out of that prison,
how to disappear afterward.</i>

40:17.332 --> 40:19.084
<i>It's all there.</i>

40:19.376 --> 40:24.131
I promise you it's only a matter of time
before we know everything...

40:24.298 --> 40:26.883
...that is in Scofield's head.

40:27.217 --> 40:29.511
<i>Where he plans to run to,
how he plans to get there.</i>

40:29.678 --> 40:31.847
<i>So when the time comes
that he does get there...</i>

40:33.223 --> 40:35.309
...we'll be waiting for him.

41:22.981 --> 41:25.067
[ENGLISH SDH]
